--- !u!114 &688950667
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 688950665}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: ea1c59ace054e0f4cb9e17e1e77a9b89, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Dialogue
  dialogueBox: {fileID: 0}
  textComponent: {fileID: 634062145}
  lines:
  - 'The jar dissolved. Into dust. Into nothing. '
  - "Together with it, the ink in the pen's reservoir began to fade \u2014 slowly,
    gently, the warmth ebbing from the nib as though something that had been burning
    very bright was finally being allowed to rest. It's journey has finnally reached
    an end."
  - Nesia held the pen up and watched the last glow of it.
  - "(Not yet. Please \u2014 not yet. I need you to get me out first.)"
  - "One last warmth. One last pulse. A straight corridor opened to the outside \u2014
    wide and clear, lit by sourceless torches. "
  - She began to run.
  textSpeed: 0.05
  playerTag: Player
  triggerOnce: 1
